# AI Assessment Scanner Rules

Before making changes, read `docs/ai-engineering/project-direction.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CODEX.md`, and `docs/ai-context/current-state.md`.

Use the canonical direction doc for product purpose, terminology, priorities, and mock/demo policy.

Keep implementation practical:

- Assessment-first, testing-first, and evidence-first.
- Modular monolith.
- API-first boundaries.
- One Linux VM and Docker Compose.
- One or two operators.
- Honest empty states instead of fake operational activity.

Scanner integrations must use adapters. The platform validates targets, executes external tools, preserves raw output, normalizes findings, links evidence, and scores risk.

Avoid broad rewrites, duplicate docs, Kubernetes, microservices, distributed workers, multi-tenant SaaS assumptions, scanner internals, governance-heavy language, roadmap labels in UI copy, and chatbot-first layouts.

When implementation status changes, update `docs/ai-context/implementation-status.md` and the relevant todo file.
